{
  "id": "phase-rs_phase_1804",
  "repo_name": "phase-rs/phase",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/phase-rs/phase",
  "base_commit": "8be55236f5f1f280489a14e736f5496a67e91fe7",
  "pr_number": 1804,
  "issue_number": 1803,
  "issue_title": "parser: cost-consequence \"unless\" clauses fall to Unimplemented instead of routing to UnlessPaymentChooseCost",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nCost-consequence \"unless\" clauses \u2014 `[effect] unless [player] [pays/does cost]` \u2014 fall through to `Effect::Unimplemented` even though the engine resolution path for them already exists. Examples: \"Sacrifice ~ unless you pay its mana cost\", \"Counter that spell unless its controller pays {3}\", \"Each player loses 3 life unless they sacrifice a creature\", \"~ deals 2 damage to that player unless they sacrifice that artifact\".\n\nThe parser only handles the **condition** form of \"unless\" (a game-state gate). The **cost-consequence** form is unparsed, so a whole class of mainstream cards is unsupported despite the runtime machinery being in place.\n\n## Existing infrastructure (resolution side is already built)\n\nThe engine already models \"do X unless a player pays/does a cost, otherwise X happens\":\n\n- `AbilityDefinition.unless_pay` \u2014 uniform field holding the unless payment (`crates/engine/src/game/coverage.rs:6059`).\n- `WaitingFor::UnlessPaymentChooseCost { costs, pending_effect, .. }` \u2014 prompts a player to pay one of several costs and applies `pending_effect` if they decline (`crates/engine/src/types/game_state.rs:2470`). Already drives Tergrid's Lantern (\"unless they sacrifice a nonland permanent\").\n- `UnlessCostBranch { Decline, Pay { index } }` + `handle_unless_payment` resolver (`crates/engine/src/types/actions.rs:83`).\n- `UnlessPayScaling` for combat-tax cases (`crates/engine/src/types/ability.rs:3741`).\n\n## The gap (parser routing only)\n\n`crates/engine/src/parser/oracle_effect/conditions.rs:435` splits on `\" unless \"` and calls `try_nom_condition_as_unless`, which only succeeds when the tail is a **game-state condition** (`parse_inner_condition` \u2192 negated gate, e.g. \"unless ~ entered this turn\"). When the tail is a **cost/consequence** (\"unless you pay its mana cost\", \"unless they sacrifice a creature\"), `parse_inner_condition` fails, the function returns `None`, and the effect falls to `Unimplemented` \u2014 surfacing as the `Effect:Unsupported unless clause` coverage handler.\n\nThe post-\"unless\" tail decomposes into three independent, typed axes that should be composed with `alt()` (per the nom mandate), not enumerated:\n\n1. **Payer scope** \u2014 `you` / `its controller` / `that player` / `each player` / `defending player`. Reuse the existing player-scope enum (`PlayerScope` / `ControllerRef`); no new bool.\n2. **The cost** \u2014 `pay {mana}` / `pay N life` / `sacrifice <filter>` / `discard a card` / `exile <filter>` / `mill N`. Reuse `parse_single_cost` \u2192 `AbilityCost`.\n3. **The consequence** \u2014 the effect parsed *before* \"unless\" becomes the `pending_effect`.\n\nMost affected cards are permutations of {payer} \u00d7 {cost} \u00d7 {consequence}, which is why one composed parser branch covers the class.\n\n## Coverage impact\n\nFrom the published coverage snapshot (`top_gaps` handler `Effect:Unsupported unless clause`):\n\n- **69 single-gap cards** (this is the only thing blocking them) out of 78 total.\n- **Independence ratio 0.88** \u2014 near-zero co-occurrence with other gaps; fixing this alone flips them green.\n- **58/69** are Commander/Legacy/Vintage-legal; 31 Modern, 21 Pioneer, 6 Standard.\n\nRepresentative cards: \"Sacrifice ~ unless you pay its mana cost\", \"Counter that spell unless its controller discards a card\", \"Counter that spell or ability unless that player pays N life\", \"Each player loses N life unless they sacrifice a nontoken creature of their choice\", \"~ deals N damage to that player unless they sacrifice that artifact\".\n\n## Proposed fix shape\n\nIn `conditions.rs`, when `try_nom_condition_as_unless` returns `None`, attempt to parse the tail as a **payment** (payer scope \u00d7 `AbilityCost`) and emit the pre-\"unless\" effect as `pending_effect`, wiring it into the existing `unless_pay` / `UnlessPaymentChooseCost` path. No new resolver logic \u2014 the change is parser routing into machinery that already exists.\n\nRegistration points to verify (per `/add-engine-effect`): parser branch (new); types (likely none \u2014 only add a payer-scope variant via `/add-engine-variant` if one is genuinely missing); resolver (verify `each player`/`that player` symmetric routing); AI legal actions for `UnlessCostBranch`; the `UnlessPaymentChooseCost` frontend overlay renders for the new sources.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Cost-consequence \"unless\" clauses parse into the existing `unless_pay` / `WaitingFor::UnlessPaymentChooseCost` path rather than `Effect::Unimplemented`.\n- [ ] Payer scope (`you` / `its controller` / `that player` / `each player` / `defending player`) is represented with the existing typed player-scope enum \u2014 no new bool.\n- [ ] Cost forms reuse `parse_single_cost`; the pre-\"unless\" effect becomes `pending_effect`.\n- [ ] The condition form of \"unless\" (`try_nom_condition_as_unless`) is unchanged \u2014 no regression on existing condition-gated cards.\n- [ ] Building-block parser tests cover payer \u00d7 cost permutations (not single-card replays).\n- [ ] `./scripts/check-parser-combinators.sh` clean; `cargo parser-gaps` shows the `Effect:Unsupported unless clause` cluster collapse; `cargo semantic-audit` introduces no misparses.\n- [ ] CR annotations verified against `docs/MagicCompRules.txt` (the existing `UnlessPaymentChooseCost` path cites **CR 118.12a** for the disjunctive sub-cost choice \u2014 confirm and cite the authorizing consequence rules per card).\n\n## References\n\n- `crates/engine/src/parser/oracle_effect/conditions.rs:435` \u2014 the `\" unless \"` split / `try_nom_condition_as_unless` boundary where cost-consequence clauses currently fail.\n- `crates/engine/src/types/game_state.rs:2470` \u2014 `WaitingFor::UnlessPaymentChooseCost` (CR 118.12a).\n- `crates/engine/src/types/actions.rs:83` \u2014 `UnlessCostBranch` / `handle_unless_payment`.\n- `crates/engine/src/game/coverage.rs:6059` \u2014 `AbilityDefinition.unless_pay`.\n- Coverage data: `top_gaps[handler=\"Effect:Unsupported unless clause\"]` \u2014 69 single-gap cards, 0.88 independence.",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-01T23:44:25.000Z",
